# Find an Object (Truck) Manually

We will go through how a human finds an object manually in an image. Then we will transition to python code.

Algorithm:

1\. Specify top left corner point of truck as (x,y) coordinate

2\. Specify bottom right corner point of truck as (x,y) coordinate

3\. Draw colored rectangle around located truck

4\. Display detected truck

## Draw Rectangle Around Truck

We will need to specify the top left corner point and the bottom right corner point of the truck. Once both points are specified, then we can use **OpenCV** function **cv2.rectangle(image_color, top_left, bottom_right, (0,0,255), 5)** to draw the rectangle. We display the located truck using **Matplotlib** function **plt.imshow(image_color)**.
